        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 16
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (A59):</strong> the <strong>belier devil</strong> (bdellavritra) behind the throne — a wormlike horror of three vile faces, styled <em>Lord of the Bloody Quicksands</em> (his name means 'Leech Master'). He served Runelord Sorshen in old Thassilon, brokered Ileosa's contract and the Crown's forging in A90, and has <strong>possessed Togomor for years</strong> as his public face — Ileosa entrances him as Sorshen once did. He lairs in the royal bedroom (A59) and manifests only when Togomor dies, when the PCs reach that room — or at once, if they enter the castle <em>ethereally</em>. A devil worth out-maneuvering rather than out-fighting.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
